This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it focuses on network algorithms and forwarding information base (FIB) design. It also mentions the programmable network framework, which is a key concept in the field of network architecture. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Programming Languages (cs.PL) as these fields are relevant to the development and implementation of the Othello Hashing algorithm and the Concise FIB design.
